(4). A, the codex Ambrosianus, now in the Ambro- sian Library at Milan. It was discovered by A. Mai in the Ambrosian Library. It is probably of the 5th century; but in the 8th century it was washed and scraped to receive a copy of the Book of Kings. Thus the original writing was greatly obliterated, but much of it has been deciphered by the successive labours of Mai himself, Schwarzmann, Ritschl, Gep- pert‚ and Studemund‚
